extra_section:
Announcement: Thank you to all of the parents who attended the parent meeting! For those unable to attend, a recording is available and the slides are linked to Lesson 15 in the Student app. A summary of key points:
The Fall semester has ended! Think Academy will begin Spring classes between January 7-11
Please have your student complete the final stage test ASAP. It is linked in the student app after lesson 15.
If textbooks have not arrived before class begins, and if coin mall prizes have not arrived by mid-January, please let us know. 
A Winter Break practice packet will be sent out on December 16 to review past material and prepare for the semester. 
Please take this survey with your student to let us know what you like about Think and how we can do better. Your student will receive 2025 coins for submitting, and 10 lucky parents will win a $50 Amazon gift card. 
English version: https://v.wjx.cn/vm/OtwpN5t.aspx 
Chinese version: https://v.wjx.cn/vm/tgGeJdy.aspx

Feedback is below.

notes: IMPORTANT: THE "UNANSWERED" QUESTIONS ARE NOT ACTUALLY UNANSWERED, BUT THEY ARE A TYPE OF QUESTION CALLED A GRAFFITI POST WHICH CANNOT BE GRADED AND THEREFORE IS LABELED AS UNANSWERED. GRACE'S SUBMISSIONS FOR THE GRAFFITI POSTS CAN BE VIEWED IN THE LESSON REPORT

notes: I already sent a version of this feedback email where I mistakenly said that Olivia was absent when she was present, because I sent to the wrong Olivia's parent. Apologize for the error and clarify that this is the correct report.

extra_feedback: Coco struggled with English, which is understandable given the recent move to the US from China. She may have a good grasp of the math concepts, but it is difficult to tell with English instruction. This week's lesson was particularly heavy in reading and understanding English since we were writing algebraic expressions to represent different situations. I would recommend that she take a Chinese math evaluation if possible, and that if she continues with Think, she registers for a class with a teacher fluent in Chinese (there are many!).

If textbooks have not arrived before class begins, and if coin mall prizes have not arrived by mid-January, please let us know. 
A Winter Break practice packet will be sent out on December 16 to review past material and prepare for the semester. 
Please take this survey with your student to let us know what you like about Think and how we can do better. Your student will receive 2025 coins for submitting, and 10 lucky parents will win a $50 Amazon gift card.

Chinese version: https://v.wjx.cn/vm/tgGeJdy.aspx

Feedback is below.
notes: The student was taking a trial class and has not signed up for long-term classes yet. Be extra warm and friendly.
